{"id":14881754,"mediaExerciseId":"179f9827-e779-4dbd-b9fd-a902d56a42f6","exerciseName":"3","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"21.3","sectionTitle":"Purchasing Power Parity","pageNumber":721,"solutions":[{"id":5966026,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we will learn the concept of absolute purchasing power parity and relative purchasing power parity. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"A **purchasing power parity** refers to the thought that the exchange rate adjusts in order to keep a *constant purchasing power* among the currencies. There are **two forms** of PPP, the *absolute* PPP and *relative* PPP.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/9b87da76cf52d8ea51e1c506e27aa7e1/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/9b87da76cf52d8ea51e1c506e27aa7e1/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"## 3a.\n\nWe are asked to define an absolute purchasing power parity and determine the reason why might it not hold for many types of goods.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":138,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/6e95f7f40df4767552475a59fb7d98a1/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/6e95f7f40df4767552475a59fb7d98a1/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"An **absolute purchasing power parity** refers to the concept of having a *same commodity cost* regardless of the currency used to purchase or sell it. If you have $1 that can buy you a Coca-Cola in US, absolute PPP indicates that you can also buy one Coca-Cola for $1 anywhere in the world.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"For absolute PPP to be hold absolutely, the following must be **true**:\n1. The transaction cost must be **zero**.\n2. There must be **no barriers** such as tariffs and taxes\n3. The commodities to be sold or purchased must be **identical** to both countries.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/ef9c650aaac65d196991c0c5b6b34d46/lateximg_large.png","width":1356},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/ef9c650aaac65d196991c0c5b6b34d46/lateximg.png","width":677}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Many commodities do not follow the assumptions since the transaction costs nowadays are not free and barriers are a must. Hence, only the **very uniform goods** can apply absolute PPP.\n\\\nAs a conclusion, it might not hold for many types of goods since the assumptions are only applicable to very uniform goods.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":138,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/d345c3d75353511d72f31057bc87b5fa/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/d345c3d75353511d72f31057bc87b5fa/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"## 3b.\n\nWe are asked to determine the change in exchange rates based on relative purchasing power parity.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":179,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/5a29e35ba14b4d5c85b335cf2034dc69/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/5a29e35ba14b4d5c85b335cf2034dc69/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"A **relative purchasing power parity** refers to the concept that there is a *change in exchange rate* that can be determined by the *difference of the inflation rate* of two countries.  ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8},{"columns":[{"text":"The formula to determine the exchange rate based on the relative purchasing power parity is as follows:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{$E(S_{1})$} &=\\text{$S_{0}$}\\times [ 1+\\text{($h_{FC}$-$h_{US}$)}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nwherein:\n$E(S_{1})$ = Expected exchange rate in *t* periods\n$S_{0}$ = Current spot exchange rate \n$h_{FC}$ = Foreign country inflation rate\n$h_{US}$ = Inflation rate in the US","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":104,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/6957816a89c101a2faf911dbf417714a/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":52,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/6957816a89c101a2faf911dbf417714a/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":9},{"columns":[{"text":"Therefore, the difference of the inflation rate of two countries determines the change in exchange rates.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":267,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/b55bbf069228cc21e0353b306c13773b/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":134,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/b55bbf069228cc21e0353b306c13773b/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":10},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, we have learned the concept of absolute purchasing power parity and relative purchasing power parity. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/57db9d9675e2ed9e2da758ea080be4ce/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/fbf0e1ff8e21709e9812134561bab1d4/57db9d9675e2ed9e2da758ea080be4ce/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":11}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"fffeca64-552c-4b04-8320-df9401cffde5","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":11}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881755,"exerciseName":"4","page":725,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"06e2b7f1-5a8b-4ac0-8dbc-7cef70e42e8a","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-exercises-4-06e2b7f1-5a8b-4ac0-8dbc-7cef70e42e8a"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881753,"exerciseName":"2","page":718,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"b67e07ff-5aa9-49b1-ab41-5bf8fe2e3f81","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-exercises-2-b67e07ff-5aa9-49b1-ab41-5bf8fe2e3f81"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-exercises-3-179f9827-e779-4dbd-b9fd-a902d56a42f6"}